Introduce a new metrics table to reduce disk usage and partition sizes', 'distinct': False, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/xgerman/cassandra-reaper/commits/fca00c49a8249e5952ac3bafd754e8dfd272f9df'}, {'sha': '2a676b049b73c31a4162c990f731263be3c21127', 'author': {'email': 'alex@thelastpickle.com', 'name': 'Alexander Dejanovski'}, 'message': "Lighten the load on Cassandra backend with less repair_run scans

Reaper checks the running and paused repair runs every 10 to 30 seconds to perform maintenance operations.
When the repair history starts growing, Reaper will scan them all to look for running/paused repairs because the repair_run_by_cluster table doesn't contain the repair run state.
This commit adds this column, which allows to filter runs early in the process instead of scanning them all in the repair_run table.
Filter runs by state in the repair_run_by_state table to avoid reading them all from the repair_run table.
Push limit from the UI to the DAO to avoid reading more repair runs from the database than required.", 'distinct': False, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/xgerman/cassandra-reaper/commits/2a676b049b73c31a4162c990f731263be3c21127'}, {'sha': '10d01edaef978f34b74e96e0e0c3f3965e0a95c3', 'author': {'email': 'alex@thelastpickle.com', 'name': 'Alexander Dejanovski'}, 'message': 'Avoid touching preinstalled JDKs in GHA when setting up CCM', 'distinct': False, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/xgerman/cassandra-reaper/commits/10d01edaef978f34b74e96e0e0c3f3965e0a95c3'}, {'sha': 'b9c4c8996c9a13cace83dbf28a3cba656cbcada8', 'author': {'email': 'mck@apache.org', 'name': 'mck'}, 'message': 'fix typo: `s/double-locking-idiom/double-checking idiom/`', 'distinct': False, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/xgerman/cassandra-reaper/commits/b9c4c8996c9a13cace83dbf28a3cba656cbcada8'}, {'sha': '29c15601422e5c20e8750d9fe4339c0d7180ad42', 'author': {'email': 'anthony@thelastpickle.com', 'name': 'Anthony Grasso'}, 'message': 'ISSUE #900: CI config updates
